{"id": "EUVD-2022-54666", "enisaUuid": "19867626-6cdd-3992-9ff5-ad6202b73670", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncrypto: qat - fix memory leak in RSA\n\nWhen an RSA key represented in form 2 (as defined in PKCS #1 V2.1) is\nused, some components of the private key persist even after the TFM is\nreleased.\nReplace the explicit calls to free the buffers in qat_rsa_exit_tfm()\nwith a call to qat_rsa_clear_ctx() which frees all buffers referenced in\nthe TFM context.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T02:23:11", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:46:38", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a843925e0287eebb4aa808666bf22c664dfe4c53", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0f967fdc09955221a1951a279481b0bf4d359941", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/80a52e1ee7757b742f96bfb0d58f0c14eb6583d0"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49566"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "2380ede2-8bf1-3713-86a4-70db759a0588", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "879f77e9071f029e1c9bd5a75814ecf51370f846 <0f967fdc09955221a1951a279481b0bf4d359941"}, {"id": "23a7234a-c038-3012-9cc1-b93848a67545", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.58"}, {"id": "40561ac2-9528-30e5-ad11-26c3a2a86a79", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "44478a7e-361e-3dae-a12b-afb7141fc454", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4.8"}, {"id": "5c9e705f-0940-3a6d-bd01-87e3546c5971", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "879f77e9071f029e1c9bd5a75814ecf51370f846 <a843925e0287eebb4aa808666bf22c664dfe4c53"}, {"id": "5dff7ffd-289e-3a79-ba09-50ad98ba1128", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "879f77e9071f029e1c9bd5a75814ecf51370f846 <80a52e1ee7757b742f96bfb0d58f0c14eb6583d0"}, {"id": "7007b19a-490a-394e-9a40-b14753d0f57f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "pro